Line Follower Robot Using Arduino (Work in Progress)

This project is an implementation of a Line Follower Robot using an Arduino Uno. The robot is designed to detect and follow a black line on a light-colored surface using IR sensors and control two DC motors through an L293D motor driver.

Note: This project is currently incomplete and represents the hardware setup and initial stages of development. Motor control logic and line-following algorithms are still under implementation.

Features
Arduino-based line follower robot.
Uses two IR sensors for line detection.
Controls two DC motors through an L293D motor driver.
Differential drive mechanism for steering.
Modular design for future enhancements.

Working Principle
Two IR sensors are placed underneath the robot to detect the line on the ground.
The sensors continuously monitor the surface and send digital signals to the Arduino.
Based on the sensor readings, the Arduino determines whether the robot should:
Move forward
Turn left
Turn right
Stop (if no line is detected)
The Arduino controls the DC motors through the L293D motor driver to perform the required movement.
The process repeats continuously, allowing the robot to follow the path.
